The paper discusses the technical and human factors involved in hardware reverse engineering, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the potential for interdisciplinary research encompassing both technical and psychological perspectives, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), robotics (cs.AR), and systems and control (cs.SY).
